    },
    {
      "para_id": "p6",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "Digital Fairness Act"
      ],
      "ordinal": 6,
      "text": "The European DIGITAL SME Alliance is Europe's largest association of ICT small and medium-sized enterprises, representing over 45,000 tech small and medium enterprises from across the continent.",
      "char_len": 194,
      "chunk_word_count": 28,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9404761904761905,
        "digit": 0.02976190476190476,
        "non_space": 0.865979381443299
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.6498015873015873,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p7",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "Digital Fairness Act"
      ],
      "ordinal": 7,
      "text": "The rapid evolution of the digital sector presents strong opportunities for innovation, growth, and employment beyond the European continent. As digital markets mature, ensuring fair competition and effective enforcement becomes critical, particularly for SMEs. In light of the growing dominance of a few global players, maintaining a level playing field is essential to support a resilient and autonomous European digital ecosystem.",
      "char_len": 433,
      "chunk_word_count": 61,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9785522788203753,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8614318706697459
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9839142091152815,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p8",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "Digital Fairness Act"
      ],
      "ordinal": 8,
      "text": "Manipulative practices and toxic business models that harm consumers and distort competition must be effectively addressed. A fair digital marketplace depends on robust action against such practices. At the same time, it is worth questioning whether new layers of regulation - as proposed through the Digital Fairness Act (DFA) - truly support these goals, or whether they risk overburdening European companies without effectively addressing market imbalances. Better enforcement of existing rules could offer a more targeted and proportionate response, especially in light of the Commission's ongoing efforts toward simplification. Should new legislation prove necessary, it should mirror the DSA and DMA's approach by targeting large platforms where these harmful practices are concentrated.",
      "char_len": 793,
      "chunk_word_count": 110,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9780058651026393,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8600252206809584
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9835043988269796,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p9",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "Digital Fairness Act"
      ],
      "ordinal": 9,
      "text": "Please find below DIGITAL SME Alliance's initial position on the Digital Fairness Act initiative. A final version will be published following further consultation with the organisation's members.",
      "char_len": 195,
      "chunk_word_count": 27,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9763313609467456,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8666666666666667
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.6614151873767259,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p10",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "Digital Fairness Act"
      ],
      "ordinal": 10,
      "text": "&gt; About the necessity of the Act. The introduction of a new legislative instrument should be considered only after excluding any possibility of effectively addressing the objectives at stake through the existing regulatory framework. Especially as the European Commission placed simplification at the core of its 2025 agenda, it is essential to critically assess whether the introduction of new digital legislation genuinely contributes to this goal.",
      "char_len": 453,
      "chunk_word_count": 66,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9742268041237113,
        "digit": 0.010309278350515464,
        "non_space": 0.8565121412803532
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9806701030927836,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p11",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "Digital Fairness Act"
      ],
      "ordinal": 11,
      "text": "Many practices the DFA aims to tackle are already covered by the digital rulebook. Some examples:",
      "char_len": 97,
      "chunk_word_count": 16,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.975609756097561,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.845360824742268
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.49281842818428184,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p12",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "Digital Fairness Act"
      ],
      "ordinal": 12,
      "text": "the DSA addresses dark patterns in Art. 25(1)",
      "char_len": 45,
      "chunk_word_count": 9,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.8421052631578947,
        "digit": 0.07894736842105263,
        "non_space": 0.8444444444444444
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.33157894736842103,
        "flags": [
