    },
    {
      "para_id": "p18",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "Digital Fairness Act"
      ],
      "ordinal": 18,
      "text": "These issues could be further **addressed through broader interpretation or targeted adjustments to existing legislation**, potentially reducing the need for new regulatory instruments.",
      "char_len": 185,
      "chunk_word_count": 23,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9631901840490797,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8810810810810811
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.5904481935923653,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p19",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "Digital Fairness Act"
      ],
      "ordinal": 19,
      "text": "**Legislative intervention should be** a. **limited to clearly uncovered areas**, such as influencer misconduct and harmful practices in gaming platforms, where EU-level rules are currently lacking, despite some national initiatives., b. **applied exclusively to large technology undertakings**, in line with the thresholds and criteria established under the Digital Markets Act (e.g. Art. 3, identification of gatekeepers) and the Digital Services Act (e.g. Articles 19 and 29, exclusion of SMEs from the scope of the obligations).",
      "char_len": 532,
      "chunk_word_count": 77,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9170305676855895,
        "digit": 0.010917030567685589,
        "non_space": 0.8609022556390977
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9377729257641922,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p20",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "Digital Fairness Act"
      ],
      "ordinal": 20,
      "text": "&gt; **About the principles.** If legislative intervention is anyway deemed necessary, it should follow the following objectives:",
      "char_len": 129,
      "chunk_word_count": 17,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9203539823008849,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.875968992248062
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.46665437561455264,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p21",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "Digital Fairness Act"
      ],
      "ordinal": 21,
      "text": "i. **Clarity and specificity**. Provisions must be clearly defined and aligned with existing frameworks (particularly with AI Act, DMA, DSA, GDPR, and Unfair Commercial Practices Directive). This is essential to facilitate implementation by avoiding overlaps or interpretative loopholes that could be exploited to the detriment of fair competition. ii. **Completeness and coherence**. Legislation should be comprehensive enough to minimise the future need for additional regulatory layers. A limited number of well-crafted, robust instruments can foster a more effective enforcement, particularly against those actors that may seek to leverage their market position through unfair practices. iii. **Harmonisation across legal systems**. Ensuring consistency across Member States will help prevent fragmentation. It is essential to ensure legal certainty.",
      "char_len": 854,
      "chunk_word_count": 115,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9554054054054054,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8665105386416861
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.966554054054054,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p22",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "Digital Fairness Act"
      ],
      "ordinal": 22,
      "text": "&gt; **About the impact on SMEs.** It is fundamental to consider the potential challenges that new legislation may pose for small and medium enterprises, as they represent a key driver of Europe’s sovereign digital innovation:",
      "char_len": 226,
      "chunk_word_count": 36,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9479166666666666,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8495575221238938
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.7776041666666667,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p23",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "Digital Fairness Act"
      ],
      "ordinal": 23,
      "text": "Compliance costs, including legal advice and consultations, may be disproportionately high for smaller companies.",
      "char_len": 113,
      "chunk_word_count": 14,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.97,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8849557522123894
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.45805555555555555,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p24",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "Digital Fairness Act"
      ],
      "ordinal": 24,
      "text": "Stricter rules could limit business activities and slow growth, as SMEs already face significantly higher market entry barriers compared to large companies.",
      "char_len": 156,
      "chunk_word_count": 22,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9851851851851852,
