    {
      "para_id": "p31",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "Digital Fairness Act"
      ],
      "ordinal": 31,
      "text": "To ensure a fair and effective regulatory environment for SMEs, the following principles should guide the implementation of new rules:",
      "char_len": 134,
      "chunk_word_count": 20,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9826086956521739,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8582089552238806
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.5591787439613527,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p32",
      "section_id": "s1",
      "section_path": [
        "Digital Fairness Act"
      ],
      "ordinal": 32,
      "text": "i. A size-based approach and an exclusion clause for micro and small enterprises that differentiate companies based on their actual market impact, ensuring proportionality and preventing undue burdens. Compliance obligations should scale with market power and data-processing capabilities. ii. The creation of the necessary tools (e.g. guidelines, help-desk, pre-filled documents and standards) to be established timely, providing direct support for implementation and enforcement, consequently minimising the economic impact of the new legislation on companies. iii. Flexible, phased implementation timelines, allowing companies adequate time to comply. iv. Strong enforcement targeted at large actors and VLOPs, whose conduct significantly affects market fairness.",
      "char_len": 766,
      "chunk_word_count": 101,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9625187406296851,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8707571801566579
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9718890554722639,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p33",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "Conclusions"
      ],
      "ordinal": 33,
      "text": "Given that the existing EU digital rulebook already addresses many of the challenges the Digital Fairness Act aims to tackle, the necessity of new legislation should be carefully evaluated. Strengthening enforcement and making targeted improvements to current frameworks should remain the primary focus.",
      "char_len": 303,
      "chunk_word_count": 43,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9885057471264368,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8613861386138614
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9149904214559388,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p34",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "Conclusions"
      ],
      "ordinal": 34,
      "text": "If new rules are introduced, they must be clear, specific, and comprehensive to provide legal certainty and avoid overlap. For this purpose, the choice of a regulation as the legal instrument is suggested. A size-based approach is critical, with exemption clauses for micro and small enterprises and rules targeting large market actors with significant systemic impact, consistent with the designation criteria set out in the DMA and the DSA.",
      "char_len": 442,
      "chunk_word_count": 69,
      "ratios": {
        "alpha": 0.9732620320855615,
        "digit": 0.0,
        "non_space": 0.8461538461538461
      },
      "meaning": {
        "score": 0.9799465240641712,
        "flags": []
      },
      "selection": {
        "selected": true,
        "policy": "threshold+top_k"
      },
      "chunk_quality": "ok"
    },
    {
      "para_id": "p35",
      "section_id": "s2",
      "section_path": [
        "Conclusions"
      ],
      "ordinal": 35,
      "text": "SMEs have the potential to be the backbone of a European sovereign digital economy. Regulatory efforts should therefore focus on curbing unfair practices by dominant platforms, fostering a competitive and sustainable digital ecosystem that benefits all market participants and supports the growth of the European tech stack.",
      "char_len": 324,
      "chunk_word_count": 47,
